            .</p>
               <p>JOHN WILLIAMS. I am a <rs id="t18280110-202-viclabel1061" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280110-202-victim1220 t18280110-202-viclabel1061"></join>, and work for Mr. Blackwell, a builder. On the 10th of January, about a quarter-past five o'clock in the evening, I left my tools in his shed; he came to me the same night; I went to the shed, and found the tools removed from where I had left them, and placed behind the door.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280110-202-person1221">
                  JOHN 
                  BLACKWELL
               <interp inst="t18280110-202-person1221" type="surname" value="BLACKWELL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-202-person1221" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280110-202-person1221" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in my shed as my carter was putting the horse in; I heard a noise in the part we call the open shed - we looked, and found Williams stooping down behind a cart; I took him - we looked further, and<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182801100100"></xptr>in the enclosed part of the shed we found Jones, down on his face, behind another rubbish-cart, and this basket of tools was in front of that cart, between the shafts; we asked what they did there; they said they came in to sleep, and Williams pretended to rub his eyes, but they were both awake.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>JONES' Defence. I was out of work, and went there to sleep.</p>
               <p>WILLIAMS' Defence. I went there to sleep, and was asleep.</p>
               <p>JONES - GUILTY. Aged 22.</p>
               <p>WILLIAMS - GUILTY. Aged 17.</p>
               <p>
